NAME
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            switch - hardware option switch

SYNOPSYS
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            bind -a '#r' /dev

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            /dev/switch

DESCRIPTION
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            The switch device serves a one-level directory, giving
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            access to one read-only file, switch. A read returns the
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            value of the development board's option switch (DS1),
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            represented as a decimal number from 0 to 15, representing
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            four bits, each corresponding to one of the four toggles.
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            Each toggle produces the value 0 when it is set `ON' and 1
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            when it is off. Toggle 1 corresponds to bit 1<<3 in the
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            number, toggle 2 corresponds to bit 1<<2, and so on

SOURCE
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            /os/mpc/devrtc.c

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                                Inferno Manual
